reviewText:
A Reb Brown film can make any day better! This may be one of the most low budget films he's done, but Reb gives his usual 128%. I swear he says 'Move!' 19 times. Chuck Conners must've owed someone a favor as he also appears in the story. Reb usually play the good guy hero, but in Last Flight, he's a more get-the-job-done, experienced soldier. He definitely kicks some butt.

In the words of Reb Brown, 'YAHHHHH!!!'
